# Slipper LED Status Detector

## The Problem
This Christmas my awesome girlfriend got me the best present: heated
slippers.
![https://media.firebox.com/product/7228/column_grid_8/yeti-heated-slippers_20372.jpg](My sweet new slippers!)

I _suffer_ from chronically cold feet in the winter, and these do just
the trick. Mine came with batteries that charge via USB. While they're
charging the LED is
[https://www3.nd.edu/~cbailey8/blog/2017/01/06/detecting_led_changes_with_raspicam/red.jpg](red),
but when they're full they switch to
[https://www3.nd.edu/~cbailey8/blog/2017/01/06/detecting_led_changes_with_raspicam/blue.jpg](blue). I
wanted a text alert when that happened so I didn't have to keep
checking on them.

## The Solution
My whole process is outlined in my
[https://www3.nd.edu/~cbailey8/blog/2017/01/06/detecting_led_changes_with_raspicam/](blog post)

## TL;DR

I used OpenCV's Python bindings to process pictures of my slipper
batteries on a Rasperrby Pi. I schedule that script with a systemd
timer to run every minute; it sends me a text via IFTTT if they're
done charging.